Edit: I'm updating my review that I left 2 years ago. We came back to eat for takeout tonight and the food was much better. We had the impossible burger and Umami Burger, as well as fries with a side of truffle ketchup. Everything was much better this time, so I'm updating my rating to 5 stars. I appreciate that the business responded to my original review and wanted to make my experience better!  Original review: We came in for dinner last night and ordered onion rings, an umami burger and a throwback burger. The umami was good for the first 2 bites but the good rich taste tapered off for the remaining chomps. A little disappointing, definitely not the best burger in Chicago. The onion rings were incredibly undercooked, all of them had a raw batter inside. My date got a real bad stomach ache after the meal. The service was great, though. So it's got that going for it. Our sever swapped out fries for the onion rings which was nice. The side sauces were also very good.

If you want quick and reasonably priced food that is actually quite delicious, then Umami Burger is the place for you.  I've never had a bad meal here and you truly cannot go wrong, provided you like burgers.  The fries are crispy and delicious and you can order any of several of their wonderful dipping sauces.  My favorites are Diablo, Honey Mustard, Miso mustard, and Buffalo.  Drinks are solid and service is usually outstanding.  Lunch for two with tip kept us right around $40 bucks, which for Wicker Park, is pretty reasonable.  Go, eat, enjoy.  Trust me.  It's great.

Something has changed here. Up until recently, I've had nothing but excellent experiences at Umami. It was one of my favorite restaurants in the area. The food is still excellent, but the service has completely hit a wall in the past 2 months.  The most recent 3 times I've been over the past 2 months (we go relatively frequently), the service has just been so slow. Recognizing the trend, I made sure to note the times on my most recent visit. We arrived at 7:15 pm and were seated right away. We placed our order around 7:35 and didn't receive our burgers and fries until just after 8:30 pm. The restaurant was a little busy right when we arrived, but was no means packed. I can't imagine why it took an hour to receive our burgers.  The selection has also changed quite a bit. We used to love the 4 sauces that came with the fries, but now there are only 2. It seems like they're discontinuing the free sauces to encourage people to buy the specialty fries ($7). The size of a full order of fries has also decreased. We used to be able to order 2 full order of fries to split among 4 people, but now everyone pretty much needs their own order. I think this is because they've switched from a full ceramic bowl to a basket with a paper lining. It looks like you're receiving the same amount of fries, but as soon as you get through the top layer, there's not much left. $4.50 for a basket of fries should be plenty for the entire table, but it isn't.

My husband and I went in for the Impossible Burger yesterday. We are both vegan. We specifically visited for the Impossible Burger, as everyone has been raving about it. While the burger patties themselves were good, we were extremely disappointed when our burgers were delivered in lettuce rather than a bun. We didn't see any note on the menu that the vegan version wouldn't have a bun. Our server, while very sweet, also did not mention that the vegan version was bunless. We were also disappointed that there was no sauce. To me, Umami Burger must know that so many of the people buying the Impossible Burger are vegans. I don't understand why they don't offer a real burger, bun and all, for the vegan version. It's so easy to find vegan bread (we get it in the bakery section at the grocery store, nothing special) and to make a vegan sauce. I would love to come back and have that delish burger, but it just doesn't feel like a burger without the bun.
